<div class="sg-h1">Utilities</div>
<div class="sg-note sg-note--outdent">Utilities are a collection of very useful CSS rule sets, their main purpose is to prevent styles from being repeated throughout a style sheet i.e. keep things <abbr title="Don't repeat yourself">DRY</abbr>. They're similar to <a href="helpers.html">Helpers</a> with the main differences being; they're not declared via a class rather all selectors using a utility are tethered together i.e. grouped selectors and they should always be used i.e. the first resort not the last like 'Helpers'. Utilities are handled via <a href="http://sass-lang.com/docs/yardoc/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html#placeholder_selectors_">Sass placeholder selectors</a>.</div>

